import pandas as pd

# Assuming you already have filled NaN values with 0 in your DataFrames
# Read CSV files into DataFrames
marker1_rubric1 = pd.read_csv("Marker 1.1.csv")
marker2_rubric1 = pd.read_csv("Marker 2.1.csv")
marker3_rubric1 = pd.read_csv("Marker 3.1.csv")
marker12= pd.read_csv("Marker 1.2.csv")
marker22 = pd.read_csv("Marker 2.2.csv")
marker32 = pd.read_csv("Marker 3.2.csv")

# Drop unnamed columns
marker12 = marker12.loc[:, ~marker12.columns.str.startswith('Unnamed')]
marker22 = marker22.loc[:, ~marker22.columns.str.startswith('Unnamed')]
marker32 = marker32.loc[:, ~marker32.columns.str.startswith('Unnamed')]

marker21 = marker2_rubric1.iloc[1:21]

# Function to calculate and fill "Total Score" column
def calculate_and_fill_total_score(df):
    # Calculate the sum of scores for each row and fill in "Total Score" column
    df["Total Score"] = df.iloc[:, 1:-2].sum(axis=1)

# Apply the function to each DataFrame
calculate_and_fill_total_score(marker1_rubric1)
calculate_and_fill_total_score(marker21)
calculate_and_fill_total_score(marker3_rubric1)
calculate_and_fill_total_score(marker12)
calculate_and_fill_total_score(marker22)
calculate_and_fill_total_score(marker32)


# Set the display options to show more columns and rows
pd.set_option("display.max_columns", None)
pd.set_option("display.max_rows", None)

print(marker12)
print(marker22)
print(marker32)

def analyze_data(df, marker_name):
    df = df.dropna()
    

    # Identify the Overall Best App
    overall_best_app = df.loc[df["Total Score"].idxmax(), "Name"]
    overall_best_score = df.loc[df["Total Score"].idxmax(), "Total Score"]

    # Identify the Best App in Each Category
    best_in_each_category = {}
    for category in df.columns[1:-2]:  # Exclude "App", "Total Score", and "Comments" columns
        best_app_in_category = df.loc[df[category].idxmax(), "Name"]
        best_score_in_category = df.loc[df[category].idxmax(), category]
        best_in_each_category[category] = {"Name": best_app_in_category, "Score": best_score_in_category}

# Create a new DataFrame for ranking
    ranking_df = df[["Name", "Total Score"]].sort_values(by="Total Score", ascending=False)

    # Print results for the marker
    print(f"\nAnalysis for {marker_name}:")
    print(f"Overall Best App: {overall_best_app} (Total Score: {overall_best_score})")

    # Display the DataFrame for ranking
    print(f"\nRanking DataFrame for {marker_name}:")
    print(ranking_df)

# Function to calculate and fill "Total Score" column with weighted scores
def calculate_and_fill_total_score(df, weights):
    # Multiply each score by its respective weight
    weighted_scores = df.loc[:, weights.keys()] * list(weights.values())
    
    # Calculate the sum of weighted scores for each row and fill in "Total Score" column
    df["Total Score"] = weighted_scores.sum(axis=1)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
import numpy as np


# Function to create a bar chart for overall scores
def plot_overall_scores(df, marker_name):
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    sns.barplot(x="Name", y="Total Score", data=df.sort_values("Total Score", ascending=False))
    plt.title(f"Overall Scores - {marker_name}")
    plt.xlabel("App")
    plt.ylabel("Total Score")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha="right")
    plt.show()

# Function to create a radar chart for category-wise scores
def plot_radar_chart(df, marker_name):
    categories = df.columns[1:-2]  # Exclude "App", "Total Score", and "Comments" columns
    values = df.iloc[:, 1:-2].mean().values

    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 8))
    ax = plt.subplot(111, polar=True)
    ax.fill_between(range(len(categories)), values, color='skyblue', alpha=0.4)
    ax.plot(range(len(categories)), values, color='skyblue', linewidth=2)

    ax.set_theta_offset(np.pi / 2)
    ax.set_theta_direction(-1)
    ax.set_rlabel_position(0)

    plt.xticks(range(len(categories)), categories)
    plt.title(f"Category-wise Scores - {marker_name}")
    plt.show()

# Function to create a text summary report
def generate_summary_report(df, marker_name):
    overall_best_app = df.loc[df["Total Score"].idxmax(), "Name"]
    overall_best_score = df.loc[df["Total Score"].idxmax(), "Total Score"]

    best_in_each_category = {}
    for category in df.columns[1:-2]:
        best_app_in_category = df.loc[df[category].idxmax(), "Name"]
        best_score_in_category = df.loc[df[category].idxmax(), category]
        best_in_each_category[category] = {"Name": best_app_in_category, "Score": best_score_in_category}

    # Print text summary report
    print(f"\nSummary Report for {marker_name}:")
    print(f"Overall Best App: {overall_best_app} (Total Score: {overall_best_score})")

# Perform analysis and create visualizations for each marker
markers = [(marker1_rubric1, "Marker 1"), (marker2_rubric1, "Marker 2"), (marker3_rubric1, "Marker 3")]

for df, marker_name in markers:
    plot_overall_scores(df, marker_name)
    plot_radar_chart(df, marker_name)
    generate_summary_report(df, marker_name)

def analyze_data(df, marker_name, column_weights):
    df = df.dropna()
    
    # Extract the relevant columns for scoring
    score_columns = [col for col in df.columns if col != "Name" and col != "Total Score"]
    
    # Calculate Total Score
    df['Total Score'] = (df[score_columns] * np.array(list(column_weights.values()))).sum(axis=1)

    # Identify the Overall Best App
    overall_best_app = df.loc[df["Total Score"].idxmax(), "Name"]
    overall_best_score = df.loc[df["Total Score"].idxmax(), "Total Score"]

    # Create a new DataFrame for ranking
    ranking_df = df[["Name", "Total Score"]].sort_values(by="Total Score", ascending=False)

    # Print results for the marker
    print(f"\nAnalysis for {marker_name}:")
    print(f"Overall Best App: {overall_best_app} (Total Score: {overall_best_score})")

    # Display the DataFrame for ranking
    print(f"\nRanking DataFrame for {marker_name}:")
    print(ranking_df)

# Load your DataFrames (e.g., marker1_rubric1, marker21, marker12, marker22, etc.)

# Analyze data for MAMA.Codes with rubric 1
analyze_data(marker1_rubric1[marker1_rubric1["Name"] == "MAMA.Codes"], "Marker 1 with Rubric 1", column_weights_rubric1)
analyze_data(marker21[marker21["Name"] == "MAMA.Codes"], "Marker 2 with Rubric 1", column_weights_rubric1)

# Function to calculate weighted scores for each category based on Rubric 2
def calculate_category_scores_rubric2(df, column_weights):
    category_scores = {}
    for category, weight in column_weights.items():
        category_scores[category] = (df[category] * weight).values[0]
    return category_scores
